@startuml
left to right direction
actor "Teacher" as T
actor "Discord REST API" as D
rectangle "Student Message API" as P1
rectangle "Student message delivery" as P2
rectangle "Discord recipient lookup" as P3
rectangle "Class Channel Post API" as P4
database "students/enrollments" as DS1
database "student_discord_credentials" as DS2
database "class_discord_bindings" as DS3
T --> P1 : DM content + class/student target
P1 --> P2 : send command
P2 --> DS1 : load recipient bases
P2 --> DS2 : load Discord identities
P2 --> DS3 : load active class guilds
P2 --> P3 : bot token + guild + identity
P3 --> D : search/fetch guild member when needed
D --> P3 : Discord user id or error
P2 --> D : send direct message
P2 --> P1 : delivery results
T --> P4 : channel post content
P4 --> DS3 : load notification channel
P4 --> D : send channel message
@enduml
